        "type": "university",
        "description": "The Military Academy of Troop Officers Commander in Chief Hugo Rafael Chávez Frías (in Spanish Academia Militar de Oficiales de Tropa Comandante en Jefe Hugo Rafael Chávez Frías), is a military academy to train officers of the National Bolivarian Armed Forces of Venezuela within basic command echelons. It is also one of the two youngest component academies of the Bolivarian Military University of Venezuela, opened on June 1, 2012. Unlike the rest of the academies, the AMOTCH is a joint service academy, only serving experienced corporals and junior ranked NCOs with a potential to become officers of the Armed Forces."
