        "type": "university",
        "description": "The Military Academy of the Bolivarian Army (in Spanish Academia Militar del Ejército Bolivariano), previously called Military Academy of Venezuela, is an academy to train members of the officer corps of the National Army of the Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela, attached to Bolivarian Military University of Venezuela. It is also the oldest military academy in the country and one of the oldest in Latin America, having been founded on September 2, 1810.\nIts campus is in Fort Tiuna in Caracas, shared with the National Guard Military Academy."
