        "description": "The National Guard Military Academy (in Spanish Academia Militar de la Guardia Nacional Bolivariana), opened in 1936, is a military academy training future officers of the Venezuelan National Guard. It shares its campus in Caracas's Fort Tiuna with the Military Academy of the Bolivarian Army."
